Code used to Scale Data and Construct Score 
## Code used to Scale Data and Construct Score ##
pca.object <- soma_df_bl_impute_wide %>% column_to_rownames("PID") %>% prcomp(center=TRUE, scale.=TRUE)

soma_df_bl_impute_wide_scaled <-
  soma_df_bl_impute_wide %>% 
  column_to_rownames("PID") %>% 
  scale(center = pca.object$center, scale = pca.object$scale) %>% 
  as_tibble(rownames = NA) %>% 
  rownames_to_column("PID") %>% 
  `colnames<-`(str_remove(colnames(.), "B_"))

soma_df_pl_impute_wide_scaled <-
  soma_df_pl_impute_wide %>% 
  column_to_rownames("PID") %>% 
  scale(center = pca.object$center, scale = pca.object$scale) %>% 
  as_tibble(rownames = NA) %>% 
  rownames_to_column("PID") %>% 
  `colnames<-`(str_remove(colnames(.), "P_"))

coefs = lasso_coefs %>% filter(grepl("seq", AptName)) %>% select(SomaId, G22DURTN_score) %>% unique()
identical(coefs$SomaId, colnames(soma_df_bl_wide[-1])) # TRUE 

heritage.scores_bl <- NULL
heritage.scores_bl[[1]] = data.frame(study_id = soma_df_bl_wide$PID,
                                     score = as.matrix(soma_df_bl_wide[,overlap.aptamers_bl]) %*% as.vector(coefs[,G22DURTN_score])  
                                     )
heritage.scores_bl <- bind_rows(heritage.scores_bl, .id="id")
heritage.scores_bl <- heritage.scores_bl %>% pivot_wider(names_from = "id", values_from = "score")
heritage.scores_bl <- heritage.scores_bl %>% `colnames<-`(c("PID", "proteomic_score_pre"))
heritageDataForModels <- her_pheno_lt %>% left_join(protein_score_pre_scaled, by = "PID")

Show how the pre-training score is related to VO2 ml/kg/min

temp <- heritageDataForModels %>% mutate(d = densCols(heritageDataForModels$B_VO2MX_B_WT18, heritageDataForModels$proteomic_score_pre_scaled, colramp = colorRampPalette(rev(rainbow(10, end = 4/6)))))

ggplot(data=temp, aes(x=proteomic_score_pre_scaled, y=B_VO2MX_B_WT18)) +
  geom_point(aes(col=d)) +
  scale_color_identity() +
  theme_bw() +
  ggpubr::stat_cor(cor.coef.name = "rho", method="spearman") +
  labs(title = "CARDIA LASSO model performance",
       subtitle = "HERITAGE, N=742",
       x = "Proteomic CRF score",
       y = expression(VO[2]~max~(ml~O[2]/Kg/min)))

ggsave("report_plots/vo2max_score_plot.pdf", device = "pdf", width = 4, height = 3)

AGE

temp <- heritageDataForModels %>% mutate(d = densCols(heritageDataForModels$AGE, heritageDataForModels$proteomic_score_pre_scaled, colramp = colorRampPalette(rev(rainbow(10, end = 4/6)))))

ggplot(data=temp, aes(x=AGE, y=proteomic_score_pre_scaled)) +
  geom_point(aes(col=d)) +
  scale_color_identity() +
  theme_bw() +
  ggpubr::stat_cor(cor.coef.name = "rho", method="spearman", label.x.npc = "right", hjust=1) +

       subtitle = "HERITAGE, N=742",
       y = "Proteomic CRF score",
       x = "Age")

colorset <- c("Female" = "darkorange", "Male" = "forestgreen")

ggplot(heritageDataForModels %>% mutate(RACE = case_when(RACE == "Caucasian" ~ "White", .default = RACE)), aes(x=proteomic_score_pre_scaled)) +
  geom_density(aes(colour = SEX, linetype = RACE)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values=colorset) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = colorset) +
  labs(x = "Proteomic CRF score",
       y = "Density",
       title = "Sex and race score distribution",
       subtitle = "HERITAGE, N=742") +
  theme_bw() +
  guides(color=guide_legend(title = "Sex"),
         linetype=guide_legend(title = "Race"))

ggsave("report_plots/heritage_score_sexRace_histos.pdf", width = 4, height = 3)
